name: Take a Break to Keep Going
description:
Approaching the 10.585th mile of their adventure, their internal organs start to complain and their souls demand leisure. Some ducks in buns meet them by the river, not charging a penny unlike the taxi beaver.
Remembering the words of a cloud-riding horse; “Taking a break might be all you need, to keep the journey going and not lose your feet.” The group agrees that it makes sense, so they pause their quest and get some rest.
